In the `KafkaProducer` class, you can add a `getLogger` method to provide access to the logger instance:

```java
import org.slf4j.Logger;
import org.slf4j.LoggerFactory;

@Service
public class KafkaProducer {

  private static final Logger logger = LoggerFactory.getLogger(KafkaProducer.class);

  // ... other code ...

  public Logger getLogger() {
    return logger;
  }

  // ... other code ...

}
```

By adding this method, you can access the logger in your test cases using the `getLogger` method, as shown in the refactored test case.